This paper discusses word embeddings and their properties, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also provides a formal explanation of the phenomenon of solving word analogies with vector arithmetic, which involves mathematical concepts and could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) subfields. Additionally, the paper discusses the weighting of word vectors, which could be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
